      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DUBIOUS EXPRESS (1) on debut for Richard and Will Freedman is a great chance to open his account immediately. Has trialled four times going back to January, with the latest at Rosehill the most impressive. Well-educated and in a thin race looks the one they have to beat. IAMBUBB (3) has not been seen since tailing the field in the Group 3 Breeders over 1000m at Randwick in October. Won a trial in good style on the Illawarra Grange circuit on 6 May. Faces a far easier task to launch this prep so expect more. RAINBOW CHARLIE (4) is a Headwater colt on debut for the Widdup camp. Recent Warwick Farm trial winner who looks to have his share of talent. FINAL GIFT (2) is the most experienced runner in the field. The last couple of runs have been plain but if at his best is sure to be about the mark. PACIFIC DIAMOND (6) placed in a recent Warwick Farm trial and is not out of the equation at her first race appearance.",
